  "original_title": "\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0b9a\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0baa\u0bbf\u0ba3\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Cecil Spring released on bail",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Colombo Chief Magistrate Nandana Amarasinghe today (29) ordered the police to submit a report on the progress of investigations in the case against three suspects, including Danis Ali, accused of trespassing into the Sri Lanka Rupavahini Corporation and disrupting broadcasts.",
        "When the Magistrate's hearing was held today, Karuwathottam Police informed the court that the investigations on the first suspect, Danis Ali, have not yet been completed.",
        "Accordingly, the judge directed the police to submit a report on the progress of investigations on September 26.",
        "Also, the judge ordered the release of Cecil Vasantha, who was arrested and remanded in connection with the incident, on a cash bail of 25,000 rupees and 2 body bonds worth 5 lakh rupees each.",
        "It is noteworthy that on July 26, Danis Ali was arrested on board a SriLankan Airlines flight from Katunayake International Airport to Dubai."
      ],
